Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and sliced pepper to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir-fry until the peppers have softened and the chicken is golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, mix together the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g}, @North Indian style spice mix{1%tsp} and half the @mango chutney{80%g}.

Once the chicken is cooked, stir the mixture into the pan until the chicken and peppers are fully coated.

Pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} onto a #baking tray{} and into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Pop the tortillas (3 per person) onto your plates and share out half the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} in the centre of each one.

Top with the @wild rocket{20%g} and mango chutney chicken, then drizzle over the remaining mayo and mango chutney. Fold over one end to encase the filling and roll up.

Serve with the wedges alongside. Enjoy!